International exchange of information at level 3
Carrying out international information exchange in the Czech Republic
The international exchange of information enables tax officials to obtain information from other Member States on intra-Community transactions and on the taxpayers who carried them out.
Council Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003 on mutual assistance in the field of VAT, repealing Council Directive (EEC) No 218/92 (hereinafter referred to as Council Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003) ) distinguishes between two basic types of exchange of information: the exchange of information on request and the spontaneous exchange of information (without prior request).
The international exchange of information on request is made through a request for information (RFI) using the standardized SCAC form.
Tax Officers in the Czech Republic send their RFIs or their replies to the RFI received by the Finance Directorate to the CLO. It will ensure that the information provided in the standardized SCAC form is translated into the foreign language and forwarded to the other Member States.
In addition, the CLO receives requests for information (RFI) from other Member States and responses to requests sent. It handles their translation into Czech and their distribution to the competent FÄ for processing.
Article 8 of Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003 sets a period of not more than three months from the date of receipt of the request for its processing.
