Sales tax risk management
Risk management in the Czech Republic
In the Czech Republic, several organizational units at different levels of financial management deal with VAT risk management.
Within the Czech Ministry of Finance, the following organizational units are responsible for risk management and combating VAT fraud:
The Department of Value Added Tax Methodology and Economic Administration, or its Risk Management Unit, identifies potential risk areas for tax revenue and evaluates trends in these risks in domestic and intra-Community trade.
At national level, this body coordinates the credibility of VAT returns criteria and uses the VIES data to detect possible tax evasion related to intra-Community supplies and acquisitions.
Based on data on the trade balance of the Czech Republic, it evaluates high-risk goods, prepares conception of value-added tax risk management and cooperates with the relevant EC institutions and the other Member States in this field.
The Department of International Assistance in the field of value added tax, among other things, exchanges of information, contributes to the creation and maintenance of a relevant information database, evaluates the data of other Member States available in the VIES system, provides outreach, and supports other forms of intergovernmental mutual assistance Council Regulation (EC) 1798/2003.
